condition: I didn’t know what activities to do with my children
message_text: @fields.child_nickname
Ask @fields.child_nickname! By asking @fields.child_nickname what their favourite activity is, you are showing them you care. Soon they might also start asking you to join them when they’re playing!
Ask your child! By asking your child what their favourite activity is, you are showing them you care. Soon they might also start asking you to join them when they’re playing!

condition: I didn’t know how to support my partner
message_text: Ask them! By telling your partner you want to help out but don’t know how, you are showing them you care and are interested in being involved. This can also help family members understand each other better.

condition: I forgot to ask my partner if they needed help
message_text: It can be difficult to remember to ask others what they need help with. Once you start offering to help however, others may realise you want to be involved and may ask for help when they need it!

condition: I forgot to ask for help
message_text: It can be hard to ask for help. Sometimes we expect our partners to know we need help even if we don’t ask them. Once you start telling however, they will likely start offering to help more often in the future.

Sometimes it can be hard to find time during the day. Can you think of a time when you’re less busy? For example, maybe it is easier to help out with housework later in the evening when some of the children have gone to sleep. Try to see what works for you!

condition: I felt uncomfortable doing tasks I don’t normally do
message_text: Be kind to yourself - trying something new is often hard at first! Give yourself time to adjust. Also remind yourself that helping your partner with these tasks benefits the whole family!
